++ A Description of the Wonder Known As the Triliminal Gate
The Wonder takes the form of a peaked archway, constructed of pollarded oak trees that have grown over a thousand years, six cubits in height and the same in width, with a depth of a double hand-width. Eight magical runes have been carved into the surface of the doors and their shared frame: these runes are filled with a mixture of argentum, corpse-soil from the grave of a mage of great power, and hide-glue boiled from the skin of a white unicorn.

Once active, the Triliminal Gate creates a doorway into another realm. This realm is the place the --Dardics-- call the //Otherworld//. Do not attempt to pass through the doorway and enter the //Otherworld// yourself. Should any //persons// from the //Otherworld// enter ours, they must be swiftly returned to their world. The nature of our world will twist and alter them over time, leading to great suffering and, eventually, death.

An inactive Triliminal Gate is naught but wood and silver, and is easily destroyed by axe, by fire, or by Nahum’s Discorporative Breath. An active Triliminal Gate is a more difficult proposition: destroying an active Triliminal Gate risks immediate release of the energies contained within, which will lash out swiftly if not first disrupted. To determine if a Triliminal Gate is active, observe the runes carved upon it; should they glow cerulean blue in color, the Gate is active and must first be deactivated before destruction is attempted.

[[/div]]
[[div style="border:solid 1px #999999; background:#ffffff; padding:5px; margin-bottom: 10px;"]]
++ On the Deactivation of the Activated Triliminal Gate
Deactivation of an energized Triliminal Gate will require the following:

* **//Dantalion’s Improved Leyline Disruption//** (or an equivalent Spell).
* A sanctified silver athame that has never drawn blood.
* A third eye and the skill to use it well.
