++ Being a History of the Wonder’s Creation
In ancient days, there was --the Great Tyrant--, and the Empire, and the --Tyrant-- was served by the wisest of his men, the --Dardic Sorcerers--. Great was their power, and mighty their works, but the people of that Age had hearts full of fear, as a rich man fears the thief in the night.

It is said that in those days, there was [[[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-1764|an enchanted mirror which could see into other worlds.]]] Many strange wonders and people could be seen in that //Otherworld//, but the --Dardics--, whose hearts were filled with fear, saw only enemies in the face of the mirror. And so it was that, as befits the nature of those foolish sages, the Empire girded themselves for war.

In their hubris and their pride, the --Dardics-- created the foulest magic ever conceived by mortal minds: The --Unspeakable Word--, whose very memory is cursed and brings misfortune and death upon those who know its name. It was to bring The --Unspeakable Word-- into the //Otherworld// that the --Dardics-- created the first Triliminal Gate.

Although the --Unspeakable-- (and all knowledge of its making) was destroyed in the War of the Red Hand by **Our Lady**, the --Dardics-- have retained the secrets of the Triliminal Gates’ construction. It is known that the --Dardics-- utilize these lesser Triliminal Gates to travel into the //Otherworld// for the purposes of sowing death and slaughter. Such violations being hateful in the eyes of **Our Lady**, the destruction of a Triliminal Gate must be considered an unambiguous good.

