++ On the //Otherworld//, and its nature.
These are the things that we know about the //Otherworld//.

The Gods of //that place// hold little power compared to our own. Sunlight will not harm you there, for the Sun of //that world// never awoke to its hateful purpose.  However, **Her Dark Majesty** also has no power in //that place//: do not rely upon the shadows to shroud you in the //Otherworld//.

Magic exists in that place, but in a far weaker state than in our own. Mages are few, work in secret, and rely on brute-force approaches. Those few of **our people** who have ventured into the //Otherworld// say that their magics would fail them: spells would not respond properly, and would often result in unanticipated side effects. Use only the least powerful of your magics in that place, and take care that your spells and fetishes do not work against you.

Names still have power in that place, but not as great a power as they do in ours. You may speak the names of the --Gods-- there and not receive harm. The people of the //Otherworld// speak the names of power without fear, for the aether of that place flows weakly, if at all, and the wind does not carry the words they speak to their gods' ears.

The people of the //Otherworld// are not gods, nor are they beasts. They live, love, hate, and war just as we do, albeit at a much quicker pace, due to their greatly shortened lives. Do not make the mistake of thinking them other than people. Consider them fellow souls, to be shepherded and protected by those greater than they.
[[/div]]
