++ Forbidding the Utilization of the Wonder, and its consequences.
**Our Lady** teaches that the weapons of --the enemy-- may be used against them, save one: **her** Edict of Forbiddance forbids passage into the //Otherworld// by any who follow her teachings.

There are three reasons for this.
* __Reason the First__, our very presence in the //Otherworld// is harmful to //those who live there//. The brilliance of our souls manifests as a twisting in their very beings, searing //their// flesh, causing sickness, twisting their bodies, and cursing //their children and their children’s children//. **Our Lady** teaches us not to cause harm to the innocent. We refuse to be the cause of harm to those who have harmed us not.
* __Reason the Second__, the actions of the --Dardics-- in the //Otherworld// has irrevocably broken the trust between our two peoples. On the few occasions that **our people** have entered the //Otherworld//, the result was violence against **our emissaries**. Many brave and kind souls fell to the //Otherworlders//’ poisoned darts and poisoned vapors, and each loss is a blade in the side of our shared people. **Our Lady** teaches us not to waste courage on fruitless endeavors. We refuse to throw away good bread into poisoned waters.
* __Reason the Third__ the method of activating Triliminal Gates is a secret jealously guarded by the --Sorcerers--. Learning this secret requires delving deep into --their forbidden knowledge--, and risking becoming tainted by --their foul beliefs--. Wise minds attempting to delve the --Dardics--’ secrets have become twisted and broken by --basilisk patterns, glyphs of madness, and soul-render vapors--. **Our Lady** teaches us that there is some knowledge which the enlightened mind must be willing to leave unknown. We refuse the pursuit of knowledge at the cost of wisdom.
[[/div]]
